Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the outer sleeve and plastic film from the top of the
@Dauphinoise Potatoes{350%grams}.

Place on a #baking tray{}. Bake on the middle shelf, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Lay the @Salmon Fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined baking tray. Spread
over the @Pesto{32%grams}, then carefully press on the @Parmigiano Reggiano{20%grams}.

Pop the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams} and @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%grams}
alongside. Drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the dauphinoise is halfway through cooking, roast the salmon and veg on the
top shelf, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Share the salmon between your plates.

Serve the dauphinoise, broccoli and tomatoes alongside.

Drizzle the @Balsamic Glaze{12%milliliter} over the veg.

Enjoy!